But on her release from hospital the bewildered little girl was told the shattering news.

The couple were gunned down during a robbery on the Puerto-Cabello to Valencia highway in Venezuela's Carabobo state on Monday. Maya was in their car with them and suffered a glancing wound to her leg during the robbery.

She was treated in hospital but did not require any surgery.

Family members arriving in Caracas from Florida, where most of Monica's family now live, told MailOnline that Maya had been allowed to leave hospital and was being cared for by her mother's cousins.

She is now expected to attend the funeral of her 29-year-old mother and ex-pat British father on Friday in Caracas.

Her fate has yet to be decided, according to her 
grandfather.

'We still 
